#Approach:

Majority Element II – Boyer Moore Voting Algorithm

Is problem me hume wo elements find karne hain jo array me n/3 se zyada baar aate hain.
Ek important observation hai ki n/3 se zyada baar aane wale elements maximum 2 hi ho sakte hain.

Isliye hum 2 candidates aur unke counts maintain karte hain.

Array traverse karte waqt:
Agar count1 zero ho jaye to current element ko candidate1 bana do.
Agar count2 zero ho jaye to current element ko candidate2 bana do.
Agar current element candidate1 ya candidate2 ke equal ho to uska count increase karo.
Agar current element dono se different ho to dono counts decrease karo.

Is process ke baad hume possible candidates mil jate hain.
Phir ek baar array traverse karke check karte hain ki wo actually n/3 se zyada baar aate hain ya nahi.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> majorityElement(int[] nums) {
        int cnt1 = 0;
        int cnt2 = 0;
        int el1 = 0;
        int el2 = 0;
        int n = nums.length;

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(cnt1 == 0 && nums[i] != el2){
                el1 = nums[i];
                cnt1 = 1;
            }
            else if(cnt2 == 0 && nums[i] != el1){
                el2 = nums[i];
                cnt2 = 1;
            }

            else if(nums[i] == el1){
                cnt1++;
            }

            else if(nums[i] == el2){
                cnt2++;
            }

            else{
                cnt1--;
                cnt2--;
            }
        }

        //Manual checking 
        int cnt1Check = 0;
        int cnt2Check = 0;

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(nums[i] == el1) cnt1Check++;
            else if(nums[i] == el2) cnt2Check++;
        }
        List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        if(cnt1Check > n/3){
            ans.add(el1);
        }
        if(cnt2Check > n/3){
            ans.add(el2);
        }

        return ans;
    }
}
